subgraph Page_27 [Page 27]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_790cba47["9.10 Satisfaction of Requirements"]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_1_f6a85290["9.10.1 The contractor shall carry out<br/>safety and systems engineering<br/>activities to provide evidence that all<br/>safety requirements, including derived<br/>safety requirements, have been met."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_2_87d1cd3a["9.10.2 The contractor shall undertake<br/>systems engineering activities which are<br/>capable of detecting counter-evidence."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_3_2e5aae6d["9.10.3 The contractor shall identify the<br/>most effective method, or methods, for<br/>showing satisfaction of requirements, or<br/>providing counter-evidence, and include<br/>this information in the SMP."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_4_6a74c91f["9.10.4 Whilst there might be general<br/>identification of techniques early in<br/>the process, the contractor shall ensure<br/>that the methods chosen are appropriate<br/>to the specific derived safety<br/>requirements identified."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_63b65d41["10 Safety Reporting"]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b["10.1 Information Set Safety Summary"]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_1_d53f0ea4["10.1.1 The contractor shall produce an<br/>ISSS as defined in the SMP."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_2_d5f3967b["10.1.2 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the ISSS contains sufficient information<br/>from the information set to enable a<br/>system integrator and a system operator<br/>to discharge their safety<br/>responsibilities."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_3_65272c13["10.1.3 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the ISSS contains information on<br/>assumptions and limitations regarding<br/>the safe use of the PSS."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_4_ce20da37["10.1.4 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the ISSS includes a justification of the<br/>scope of the information provided."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_5_7f050e3f["10.1.5 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the ISSS is delivered incrementally, as<br/>contracted and as defined in the SMP, to<br/>give the UK MOD visibility of progress<br/>in safety engineering and safety<br/>analysis."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560["10.2 Safety Case"]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_1_57e58d3a["10.2.1 The contractor shall produce a<br/>safety case or safety cases for a PSS as<br/>defined in the SMP."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_2_e98a9ad3["10.2.2 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the safety case consists of a structured<br/>argument, supported by a body of<br/>evidence that provides a compelling,<br/>comprehensible and valid case that a<br/>system is safe for a given application<br/>in a given environment."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_3_0b59a8e8["10.2.3 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the evidence for the safety case is<br/>drawn from the information set."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_4_114e8cf9["10.2.4 The contractor shall address<br/>safety throughout the life of the PSS<br/>within the safety case, to the extent<br/>required by the scope of contract."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_5_6a86a3d5["10.2.5 The contractor shall provide<br/>evidence that supports claims for the<br/>verification and validation of all<br/>safety requirements, including evidence<br/>from sub-contractors."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_790cba47 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_1_f6a85290
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_790cba47 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_2_87d1cd3a
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_790cba47 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_3_2e5aae6d
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_790cba47 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_9_10_4_6a74c91f
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_63b65d41 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_1_d53f0ea4
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_2_d5f3967b
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_3_65272c13
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_4_ce20da37
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_d59eba9b -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_1_5_7f050e3f
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_63b65d41 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_1_57e58d3a
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_2_e98a9ad3
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_3_0b59a8e8
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_4_114e8cf9
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_f5d7d560 -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_5_6a86a3d5
end
subgraph Page_28 [Page 28]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_6_6b7480bf["10.2.6 The contractor shall provide<br/>evidence of compliance with relevant<br/>legislation, regulations, standards,<br/>policy and approved codes of practice."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_7_b4115d7d["10.2.7 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>the safety case identifies how to<br/>address any residual shortfalls in<br/>meeting safety requirements."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_8_2873d0db["10.2.8 The contractor shall develop,<br/>maintain and refine the safety case as<br/>defined in the SMP."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_10_427b1d5c["10.2.10 The contractor shall provide<br/>diverse evidence, to ensure that that<br/>the overall safety argument is not<br/>compromised by errors or uncertainties<br/>in individual pieces of evidence."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_12_8ad88b8b["10.2.12 The contractor shall justify the<br/>adequacy and suitability of the methods<br/>and techniques used for hazard analysis,<br/>design for safety, safety analysis and<br/>other relevant safety engineering<br/>activities."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_3_a3d53825["10.3 Safety Case Reports"]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_3_1_d145953e["10.3.1 The contractor shall produce a<br/>safety case report or reports as defined<br/>in the SMP."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_3_2_0afffa35["10.3.2 The contractor shall produce<br/>safety case reports that incorporate the<br/>key elements of the safety argument and<br/>provision of evidence."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_3_3_0716e787["10.3.3 Where there are shortfalls in the<br/>evidence the contractor shall ensure<br/>safety case reports provide the<br/>rationale for operating the PSS, and the<br/>ways of mitigating the residual risk."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_3_4_c2f3bbd0["10.3.4 The contractor shall ensure that<br/>safety case reports contain information<br/>on assumptions and limitations regarding<br/>the safe use of the PSS."]
    DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_6_6b7480bf -->|"contains"| DEFENCE_STANDARD_00_056_PART_01_INSA_10_2_7_b4115d7d
